	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg – A man in his 40s was shot dead during a robbery at a building on Jorrisen Street in Braamfontein on Monday, authorities said. "The man was on his way to the bank when two people confronted him. They allegedly pointed a firearm at him and shot him," said Captain Kay Makhubela. He said they then robbed him of an undisclosed amount of money. "The suspects fled the scene in a blue vehicle. No one has been arrested yet," he said. Netcare 911 spokesperson Nick Dollman said they responded to the shooting at approximately 15:35. "Reports from the scene indicate that a male, believed to be approximately forty years old, had been shot several times. Tragically, the victim sustained severe injuries and died at the scene," said Dollman. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  